body:
Consider the following input:
```mlir
hw.module @Foo(in %u: i42, in %v: i42, in %w: i42, in %q: i1, in %r: i1) {
  %0 = llhd.constant_time <0ns, 0d, 1e>
  %a = llhd.sig %u : i42
  llhd.process {
    llhd.drv %a, %u after %0 : !hw.inout<i42>
    llhd.drv %a, %v after %0 if %q : !hw.inout<i42>
    llhd.drv %a, %w after %0 if %r : !hw.inout<i42>
    llhd.halt
  }
}
```
Running this through `circt-opt --llhd-mem2reg` produces this result:
```mlir
hw.module @Foo(in %u : i42, in %v : i42, in %w : i42, in %q : i1, in %r : i1) {
  %a = llhd.sig %u : i42
  llhd.process {
    %0 = llhd.constant_time <0ns, 0d, 1e>
    llhd.drv %a, %w after %0 if %r : !hw.inout<i42>
    llhd.halt
  }
}
```
Only the final drive is retained in the output. Instead, the final value should be `w` if `r`, or `v` if `q&!r`, or `u` otherwise.

